## IDE Setup

Modern Java IDEs automatically recognize Maven and Gradle projects, downloading dependencies and configuring the classpath. After adding the dependency to your build file:

1. **IntelliJ IDEA**: Open the project folder or `pom.xml`/`build.gradle` file. IntelliJ will import the project and download dependencies automatically.

2. **Eclipse**: Import as a Maven or Gradle project using the built-in import wizard. The [M2Eclipse](https://www.eclipse.org/m2e/) plugin handles Maven projects.

3. **VS Code**: Install the [Extension Pack for Java](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=vscjava.vscode-java-pack), then open the project folder. VS Code will detect the build system and configure accordingly.

For more detailed IDE setup, refer to your IDE's documentation:

